<B><a name="general">General</a> Site Requirements:</B>  Do I have the right system to use the site?<BR>
<ul>
	<li>The staff site was designed for Internet Explorer or Netscape Navigator, versions 4.0 and up on a PC.  Check your 
	browser version (found in HELP, About Internet Explorer).  These browsers are available to download for free from 
	their respective sites.</li>
   	  <center><a href="http://www.netscape.com/download/index.html"><img src="/images/netscape.gif" border=1></a>
	  <a href="http://www.microsoft.com/windows/ie"><img src="/images/ie.gif" border=1></a></center>
	<li>For the staff site to work properly, your browser needs to allow cookies. Does your computer allow "cookies"? It is a 
	setting on your browser that can be enabled or disabled. In Internet Explorer 5.0, go to the TOOLS menu. Click  
	INTERNET OPTIONS, then go to the SECURITY tab. Press the CUSTOM LEVEL button, then scroll down to the 
	Cookies section and make sure both are ENABLED.</li>
	<li>To best use the Resource Center, it is recommended that you have Adobe Acrobat installed in your system.  Most 
	resources located in the resource center are submitted in this format.  You can download the free software by clicking 
	<a href="http://www.adobe.com/products/acrobat/readstep2.html">here</a>.</li>
	<li>This site was designed for use on a PC system (IBM), not a Macintosh.  Things should function even on a Mac, but do 
	not expect the same quality of performance or support.  The Campus Ministry has asked that all Campus Staff use 
	PC's.  Please refer to the <A HREF="#what">computer requirements</a> which have been 
	in place for the Campus Ministry since 1999.</li>
</ul>
