<B><a name="tips">Tips</a> to Improve Performance:</B><BR><BR>
<UL>
	<li>If possible, use a DSL connection or some kind of high-speed connection.  If that is impossible, it's recommended that 
	you try to use the site at less busy times of the day.  If you are a modem user, your connection speed can be affected 
	by Internet traffic within the phone lines.  Many times the morning hours are a less busy time of day.</li>

	<li>When using Internet Explorer 5, performance can be affected by an inaccurate reading on your clock.  This can be 
	something as simple as the time zone being off, or even the actual time or date.  Because this is a secure Web site 
	and you are automatically logged out after 30 minutes of inactivity, it is imperative that your time be correct on your 
	computer.   </li>

	To solve this double click on the time itself, located on the bottom right hand of your screen.  Check to make sure the 
	time, the date, the am/pm and even the time zone is listed correctly.  Any one of these being inaccurate may cause 
	some pages not to function within the site.   To activate the new settings, click on "apply."</li>

	<li>Often times your computer is slowed down by the number of "Temporary Internet Files" stored on your computer, also 
	called Cookies.  Cookies are meant to help speed navigation, but when the number becomes large it can actually 
	slow down your system.  </li>

	To delete these files:  While in Internet Explorer 5.0, go to the TOOLS menu. Click INTERNET OPTIONS, and make 
	sure you are on the GENERAL tab. Click the SETTINGS button, then VIEW FILES.  Because these are "temporary 
	files" feel the freedom to delete some or all of them.  To select all of them, go to FILE and choose SELECT ALL and 
	then delete.</li>
</ul>
